<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2614708>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. A–B, Kiekie sinuatipes (F.O. Pickard-Cambridge, 1897), habitus, dorsal view. A, female; B, male." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2614708/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2614710>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Kiekie sinuatipes (F.O. Pickard-Cambridge, 1897), female. A, right chelicerae, showing the fang and the basal segment with teeth; B–F, right tarsus, leg I; B, patch of tenent setae (claw tufts, CT) arising from a movable plate (claw tuft plate, CTP); C, close up of the tip of the tenent setae; D, position of the tarsal organ (TO), arrows point the position of trichobothria; E, tarsal organ; F, trichobothrium." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2614710/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2614712>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Male metatarsus IV, left leg, ventral view. A, Kiekie sarapiqui new species; B, Kiekie sinuatipes (F.O. Pickard- Cambridge, 1897); C, Kiekie curvipes (Keyserling, 1881)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2614712/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2614714>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Kiekie sinuatipes (F.O. Pickard-Cambridge, 1897), female. A, spinnerets, overview; B, anterior lateral spinneret (ALS), with a pair of major ampullate (MAP) spigots; C, ALS close up, with a pair of MAP and a large tartipore (TP); D, posterior median spinnerets (PMS), with aciniform glands (AC) spigots, cylindrical glands (CY) spigots and a pair of minor ampullate (mAP) spigot; E, PMS close up, with a pair of minor ampullate (mAP) spigots and a large tartipore (TP); F, posterior lateral spinnerets (PLS), with cylindrical gland (CY) spigots and PLS modified spigot (MS)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2614714/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2614716>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Kiekie sinuatipes (F.O. Pickard-Cambridge, 1897). A–B, male palp; A, ventral view; B, retrolateral view; C, epigynum; D, vulva. Abbreviations: C, conductor; CD, copulatory ducts; E, embolus; FD, fertilization ducts; LP, lateral projection; MA, median apophysis; MF, median field; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; S, spermathecae; Ti, tibia." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2614716/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2614718>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Kiekie curvipes (Keyserling, 1881). A, male palp, ventral view; B, epigynum; C, vulva. Abbreviations: C, conductor; CD, copulatory ducts; E, embolus; FD, fertilization ducts; LP, lateral projection; MA, median apophysis; MF, median field; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; S, spermathecae; Ti, tibia." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2614718/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2614722>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8. Kiekie sarapiqui new species. A–B, male palp, ventral and retrolateral views; C, epigynum; D, vulva. Abbreviations: C, conductor; CD, copulatory ducts; E, embolus; FD, fertilization ducts; LP, lateral projection; MA, median apophysis; MF, median field; RTA, retrolateral tibial apophysis; S, spermathecae; Ti, tibia." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2614722/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2614734>
    dc:description "FIGURE 15. Maps representing part of Central America and north of South America, with collection localities of Kiekie species." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2614734/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

